==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gilthead
<hw>Gilt"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A marine fish.</def> The name is applied to two species:
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The <spn>Pagrus auratus</spn> (syn. <spn>Chrysophrys
auratus</spn>), a valuable food fish common in the Mediterranean (so
named from its golden-colored head); -- called also
<altname>giltpoll</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
<spn>Crenilabrus melops</spn>, of the British coasts; -- called also
<altname>golden maid</altname>, <altname>conner</altname>, <altname>sea
partridge</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

